<concept id="About_this_Manual_115" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>About this Manual</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>This manual describes the integration of the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud Web service (Amazon EC2), a major component of Amazon Web Services (AWS), with <ph
                    product="oscm_ce"><ph conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Name"/> (<ph
                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/></ph>) <ph
                    product="oscm_ee">FUJITSU Software Enterprise Service Catalog Manager, hereafter referred to as <ph
                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/></ph>.</p>
            <p>This manual is structured as follows: </p>
            <p>
                <table colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
                    <tgroup cols="2">
                        <colspec colname="col2" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col3" colnum="2" colwidth="1.43*"/>
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2">Chapter</entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">Description</entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../Intro/c_Introduction.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">Provides an overview of the <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                    /> AWS integration, the components involved, and the supported usage scenarios. </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../Services/c_ServicesIntro.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">Describes how to create and publish services for AWS in <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/>. </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../Using/c_UsingIntro.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3"
                                        >Describes how to provision and deprovision virtual servers in AWS through services in <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/>.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../Administrating/c_AdministratingIntro.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">Describes administration tasks related to the  <ph
                                    conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                /> AWS integration. </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../Appendix/r_ConfigSettingsController.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3"
                                    >Describes the configuration settings for the AWS integration software. </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../Appendix/r_ServiceParameters.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3"
                                    >Describes the technical service parameters and service operations which are supported by the AWS service controller.</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </p>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
